I have completed the review of the pull request and written the requested comments to the output file. 

The primary issue identified is that the `docker/cli` dependency bump in the root `go.mod` file was not replicated in the workspace's submodules (`cmd/krane`, `pkg/authn/kubernetes`, and `pkg/authn/k8schain`). Because these submodules utilize a `replace` directive pointing back to the root module, failure to update the versions in their respective `go.mod` files causes out-of-sync module dependencies. As a direct result, any attempt to run `go test ./...` or `go build ./...` inside them immediately fails with a `"updates to go.mod needed"` error, breaking the repository's `presubmit.sh` test suite.

The comments file has been generated with actionable paths and requests for merge-readiness.
